parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Contamination due to Improper Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil contamination can cause severe engine damage, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and potentially leaving the vehicle inoperable.
A faulty oxygen sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, potentially leading to premature engine wear.
Sudden engine stalling without warning can cause accidents, especially if it occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
The failure of the torque converter lock-up solenoid can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and driveability issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: inability to shift out of park

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, making it difficult or impossible to shift, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical components to malfunction, including turn signals, hazard lights, and airbag systems, increasing the risk of accidents and reducing vehicle safety.
